## Data cleaning & Preparation

## Goal
To clean a raw dataset by handling missing values, duplicates, and incorrect data. By:
• Identifying missing or null values
• Removing duplicates
• Correcting data formats (dates, numbers, text)

## Tool
Microsoft Excel

## Skill
Data loading and conversion
Data cleaning and preparation
Detecting duplicates

## The Process
After downloading the dataset, I changed the format from google sheets to excel.
I imported the dataset into excel and duplicated the sheet, naming one 'Raw' and the other 'Clean'
On the clean sheet, I checked for blanks and found the Coupon code had some missing cells probably because some orders did not have coupon codes.
Therefore I filled them with N/A to avoid blank spaces.
I used an excel function to create a duplicate checking column and further checked that new column to see if there were duplicates.
The dataset had zero duplicates.
I coulour coded the sheet to seperate the additional column from the original columns.

## The analysis
The dataset contains product orders where the order id, product, quantity, price, shipping address, payment method, tracking number, items in cart, coupon code, referal source and total price.
Here, each order can be tracked with order id and tracking number so if there was a case of duplicates, it ould mean that an order was either documented twice or sent twice accidentally.
The absence of the duplicates showed the orders ere'nt delivered twice.

